Time-resolved luminescence measurements were performed by using FluoroMax 4 (Horiba) in a time-correlated single-photon counting (TCSPC) mode. For excitation, a LED source (Horiba) with the excitation wavelength set to λex = 371 nm and the repetition rate set to 1 MHz was used. The resulting luminescence signal was detected at an emission wavelength of λem = 655 nm. The luminescence decay curves were fitted multiexponentially with αi being the amplitude of the ith component with the corresponding decay time τi (Eq. (1)). Additionally, the intensity-weighted average decay time τav(int), which is calculated according to Eq. (2), was used. The goodness of the fits was judged on the reduced \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
